subSubSection.paragraph:
Oligaphorura judithnajtae
n. sp. seems to be most similar to
O. duocellata
but can be distinguished from that species as the first thoracic segment has one pso (two pso in
duocellata
), the presence of one pso on each subcoxae (2,2,3 pso in
duocellata
) and by the PAO with one four-lobed vesicle (three-lobed in
O. duocellata
).
